{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017QxmPepZfK3iw5z1QbXz2D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to stop Elasticsearch first before running `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap`. I'll need to:\n1. Stop the ES process in the pod\n2. Run `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap`\n3. Start ES again\n\nBut that's complex in a Kubernetes pod. Instead, a better approach:\n1. Update the ConfigMap to remove nodes 1 and 2 from discovery seed_hosts\n2. Delete the es-cluster-0 pod to trigger a restart\n3. But BEFORE the pod starts, exec in and run unsafe-bootstrap\n4. Or... use an init container approach - too complex\nActually, the simplest approach would be to scale the StatefulSet down to zero to stop all Elasticsearch processes, then exec into a temporary pod that mounts the same PVC and run the unsafe-bootstrap command directly against the data directory, before scaling back up to one.\n\nWait, even simpler—I can just update the ConfigMap to set `discovery.type: single-node`, which bypasses the quorum requirement entirely for a single-node cluster, then restart the pod. The node should read the existing cluster state and data from the PVC and become master immediately without needing to join other nodes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2797,"cache_read_input_tokens":45241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2797},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"feb0acba-31e1-4f4c-89a9-732756f7a42b","uuid":"a143e396-2106-4d71-8c47-688f453afee0","request_id":"req_011CbztkZ6PmGZy5CoG6zZcd"}
