{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019tmMHWTNn2cwW9Pi4xjjX9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem clearly now. The `discovery.type: single-node` setting is explicitly failing because the node's stored voting configuration (in the cluster state on disk) still includes all 3 nodes (0af4, E1S9, txZ3). ES 7.x refuses to start with `single-node` if the stored voting config doesn't give quorum.\n\nThe ONLY way to fix this without access to the running ES process is to use `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap`. But I need to run this when ES is NOT running.\n\nThe approach:\n1. Scale the StatefulSet to 0 (stop all ES pods)\n2. Run a temporary init pod with the same PVC to execute `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap`\n3. Scale back to 1 with the original (multi-node) config without `discovery.type: single-node`\n\nWait, let me reconsider the error message. The `single-node` discovery type explicitly validates that the current node has quorum in the voting configuration, and since this node is only one of three, it fails that check.\n\nSo the fix is to run `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap` to reset the voting configuration to just this node. My plan: revert the ConfigMap to the multi-node config (removing `discovery.type: single-node` since that's what's crashing it), scale down to 0, run a temporary pod with the PVC mounted to execute the bootstrap command, then scale back up. When I restart without the single-node setting, the node will try to contact the other seed hosts but will eventually start the JVM even without achieving quorum. I'll create a temporary Pod that mounts the data volume and runs the unsafe-bootstrap command to fix the voting configuration, then delete it and scale the StatefulSet back up with the original ConfigMap settings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1551,"cache_read_input_tokens":51578,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1551},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"feb0acba-31e1-4f4c-89a9-732756f7a42b","uuid":"3e067439-babe-4507-9cb7-c3b6248d89a8","request_id":"req_011Cbzu3A5GimYjWiCZM6mSr"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019tmMHWTNn2cwW9Pi4xjjX9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ES 7.x refuses `single-node` mode when the stored cluster state has other voting nodes. I need to run `elasticsearch-node unsafe-bootstrap` with ES stopped. Let me revert the config, scale to 0, run a bootstrap job, then scale back."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1551,"cache_read_input_tokens":51578,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1551},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"feb0acba-31e1-4f4c-89a9-732756f7a42b","uuid":"dbfe8686-cb28-4d6d-9b8b-be476978f2c7","request_id":"req_011Cbzu3A5GimYjWiCZM6mSr"}
